node.text: “And into the forest I go to lose my mind and find my soul”.
ALL are welcome in my home. ALL are accepted and loved here.

Thank you Armstrong and Taylor Kopp for putting together another successful Walk For Hunger event (Taylor’s senior project). It was an honor to walk with you this morning. The event raised over $5400 to fight food insecurity within our community.  Proceeds are going directly to the Southwest Butler Food Cupboard and the Lighthouse Foundation.

Not going to lie...I am exhausted after another successful Community Day. Being on my township’s Recreation Board is both an honor and a labor of love (a lot of labor). We sacrifice time with our own families to bring fun, free events to our community. We do it because we love where we live and we love making people smile. Now, if you will excuse me, I am going to go float in the pool before I have to start packing for vacation. #newsewickleytownship, #givebacktoyourcommunity, #getinvolved
I asked my husband to pick me up a new cell phone case while he was out-and-about. This is what he came home with. #hesthebacontomyeggs
It’s crazy how much love I have for these goats. I definitely needed some goat therapy today. Their silliness and affection can make me smile no matter what.
A day well spent with those I love. #bradysrun #fortheloveofnature #picnic #rocktower #
